From stephane.dray at univ-lyon1.fr  Wed Jan  9 17:04:44 2013
From: stephane.dray at univ-lyon1.fr (=?ISO-8859-1?Q?St=E9phane_Dray?=)
Date: Wed, 09 Jan 2013 17:04:44 +0100
Subject: [R-sig-eco] fourthcorner() with missing data
In-Reply-To: <F28530AAD6ED02688CC820DE@BIO-BZJXM-0803.bio.bris.ac.uk>
References: <F28530AAD6ED02688CC820DE@BIO-BZJXM-0803.bio.bris.ac.uk>
Message-ID: <50ED951C.6040307@univ-lyon1.fr>

Hello,

the method does not consider missing values. The best solution would be 
to estimate missing values to fill the . For this estimation, you can 
either use the nipals method (nipals function in ade4 with rec = TRUE) 
or use the missMDA package. The second approach is better.

Cheers.

